The paper focuses on investigating the accuracy of CNNs in real-world applications with constrained time budgets, which is a common concern in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the trade-offs among different factors in network designs, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper presents an architecture that achieves competitive accuracy in the ImageNet dataset, which is a common benchmark in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
